column2: Disc was in full shade of the boat
IF TP  more than  0.2 RUN AT HIGH LEVEL
Slight brownish tint to water.  Partly cloudy.
Hazy skies- partly sunny- windy- waves.
underwater weeds at the "deep hole" site greatly reduced visibility in June and July. The August reading is a more accurate measurement of actual water clarity.
overcast- weed growth diminished- water very clear.
clear of weeds- bright sun overhead
full sun- milfoil still a problem
Eurasian milfoil growth makes accurate reading of depth very difficult.
clear sky.  Usual weed growth at testing spot.
Deep hole is totally filled with pond weeds.  Bottom is at 7 feet.  These factors affect the accuracy of the depth report.
Overcast- wind between 5 and 10 mph.  Some waves.

column1: Bright sun- light wind.  Underwater weeds are beginning to affect sunlight reaching the disk.

column2: Partly cloudy.  Measurement taken during full sun.  Weedy growth in "deep hole" area cleared by weed harvester. Partly cloudy.  Measurement taken during full sun.  Weedy growth in "deep hole" area cleared by weed harvester.
Pond refilled now after winter drawdown.  No water vegetation at sampling location.
Windy- some waves- water stirred up a bit.
Testing site continues to be free of water plants.  Rain on prior day had an effect on water clarity.  Some wind- partly cloudy.
Calm wind- bright sun.  Ospreys have returned.  Lots of turtles sunning.
Sunny- light wind making waves.  Eurasian milfoal is gone- but native vegetation is spreading throughout the pond.
Dark sky- black clouds- some wind.  Reflections on water surface affect measurement.
Sky overcast.  No direct sun.  Water reddish-brown tannin stained.  No wind.
Sunny- clear skies.  This reading is more typical of this water body than some of the earlier ones this year.
McDill Pond is being drawn down.  Leak in causeway near dam.  Water in top half is just in the channel.  Rest is mud flats.  Can't measure depth.
McDill Pond continues to be drawn down since leak in dam in 2011.  Projected to be refilled after repairs sometime toward the end of summer of 2012.  Will resume readings when pond is refilled.
Overcast- light wind.  Weed growth under control at monitoring site.
Bright and sunny- unlike previous sampling dates this year.  Wind 5mph- gusting to 10 mph.
Large amount of charra and algae
Sunny and a lot of rain in last month- high water levels
Sunnay and windy lots of brown sediment in water
sunny and warm- rain finally slowed down and cooler
Sunny and really warm- less rain- very clear water
clear- water cooling chara mats present
A lot of rain last few days- pre treatment water sample due to a lot of brown algae and nutrient concerns
A lot of rain last night flushing through McDill
Single Loon diving next to measuring location.  Sunny.  Calm wind.
Very beautiful looking with very little algae- water has started to cool.
a lot of rain and a lot of native weed growth - choking lake
Some turbidity apparently caused by strong winds yesterday that stirred up the water.
